headline: Why BTQ Technologies (NEOE:BTQ) Is Up 9.8% After Securing Nasdaq Uplisting Approval and What’s Next
summary: BTQ Technologies Corp. has received approval to list its common shares on the Nasdaq Global Market, with trading commencing under the symbol "BTQ" on September 26, 2025, and shares ceasing trading on the OTCQX but continuing on the CBOE Canada and Börse Frankfurt exchanges. This uplisting marks a key milestone for BTQ, aiming to expand funding opportunities and accelerate the commercialization of its quantum computing and post-quantum security platform. We'll explore how joining the Nasdaq,...
